    },
    {
      "id": "212018c0_a3e07f0c",
      "file_path": "cps-service/src/main/java/org/onap/cps/api/impl/CpsDataServiceImpl.java",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 78,
      "message": "CREATE operation is added only when root data-node is created. In this method, child-data node is created so the operation should be 'UPDATE'.\nMore details are provided here https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/CPS-470%3A+Spike+-+Add+support+for+data+deletion+events#CPS470:SpikeAddsupportfordatadeletionevents-Operation",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7680,
        "name": "Renu Kumari",
        "display_name": "Renu Kumari",
        "email": "kashi.renu@gmail.com",
        "username": "renukumari"
      },
      "updated": "2022-01-10 12:51:55.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "df04ec8a_98a503a0",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "cf3ee474_71724428",
      "file_path": "cps-service/src/main/java/org/onap/cps/api/impl/CpsDataServiceImpl.java",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 88,
      "message": "List Elements are not supported at the root node. All operations at the 'non-root' level are considered as 'UPDATE'. \n\nMore details are provided here https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/CPS-470%3A+Spike+-+Add+support+for+data+deletion+events#CPS470:SpikeAddsupportfordatadeletionevents-Operation",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7680,
        "name": "Renu Kumari",
        "display_name": "Renu Kumari",
        "email": "kashi.renu@gmail.com",
        "username": "renukumari"
      },
      "updated": "2022-01-10 12:51:55.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "3a6ce767_82eac865",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "a0113aba_b1a3182e",
      "file_path": "cps-service/src/main/java/org/onap/cps/api/impl/CpsDataServiceImpl.java",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 141,
      "message": "The story has been divided into two parts to make it easier to code and review.\nThis change is to add operation to already existing events. \nIn the next change, the condition will be added to identify which data node is deleted ( root or non-root) and the correct operation will be sent.\n\nIn the case of non-root data-node deletion, the operation would be 'UPDATE'. If a root data-node is deleted, the operation would be 'DELETE'. \n\nIt will be handled as part of 'https://jira.onap.org/browse/CPS-849' sub task.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7680,
        "name": "Renu Kumari",
        "display_name": "Renu Kumari",
        "email": "kashi.renu@gmail.com",
        "username": "renukumari"
      },
      "updated": "2022-01-10 12:51:55.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "b5131f79_2ee744bb",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "559267af_604344c1",
      "file_path": "cps-service/src/test/groovy/org/onap/cps/api/impl/CpsDataServiceImplSpec.groovy",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 228,
      "message": "The List elements are not supported at the root node, so all the operations on list element will be 'UPDATE'. \nhttps://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/CPS-470%3A+Spike+-+Add+support+for+data+deletion+events#CPS470:SpikeAddsupportfordatadeletionevents-Operation",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7680,
        "name": "Renu Kumari",
        "display_name": "Renu Kumari",
        "email": "kashi.renu@gmail.com",
        "username": "renukumari"
      },
      "updated": "2022-01-10 12:51:55.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "30e0983b_d3333ccd",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "c80fb4ef_6dd2ce08",
      "file_path": "cps-service/src/test/groovy/org/onap/cps/api/impl/CpsDataServiceImplSpec.groovy",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 239,
      "message": "It is to delete a non-root data node, so it will be 'UPDATE' too. But, I need to check if 'deleteDataNode' can support root data node too and a test case will be added or updated as per that. This complexity will be handled as a part of 'https://jira.onap.org/browse/CPS-849' sub-task.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7680,
        "name": "Renu Kumari",
        "display_name": "Renu Kumari",
        "email": "kashi.renu@gmail.com",
        "username": "renukumari"
      },
      "updated": "2022-01-10 12:51:55.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "53851e92_9710eca4",
      "unresolved": true
    },
