      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 37,
      "message": "Do I understand correct that for a CHILD_NODE operations the rootNodeOperation is still 'update' ?!\n(I'm still a bit puzzled to why this is needed and if theis is the best way to capture a asperate 'root' operation)\n\nI probably would prefer to see it more clearly using NO default constructor like so:\n\n\n    ROOT_NODE_CREATE(\"create\"),\n    ROOT_NODE_UPDATE(\"update\"),\n    ROOT_NODE_DELETE(\"delete\"),\n    CHILD_NODE_CREATE(\"update\"),\n    CHILD_NODE_UPDATE(\"update\"),\n    CHILD_NODE_DELETE(\"update\");\n\nand maybe expand all te string to include \"root\":  \n\n    ROOT_NODE_CREATE(\"root_create\"),\n    ROOT_NODE_UPDATE(\"root_update\"),\n    ROOT_NODE_DELETE(\"root_delete\"),\n    CHILD_NODE_CREATE(\"root_update\"),\n    CHILD_NODE_UPDATE(\"root_update\"),\n    CHILD_NODE_DELETE(\"root_update\");",
